name: The Winged Wolf
description: The Winged Wolf is, as the name implies, a wolf with wings. These vary in species (some have wings like a bird, while others have wings like a bat). The species of wing does not interchange between breed of Winged Wolf. Bird-winged wolves of a pure line do not give birth to a bat-winged wolf, nor does a bat-winged wolf of a pure line give birth to a bird-winged wolf. They can only occur in mixed litters if their parents (or ancestors are mixed lineage).
